cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SE. 

This paper presents a deep learning toolbox that allows users to train models without writing code, making it relevant to several sub-categories. The focus on deep learning and model building suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The use of declarative configuration files and the emphasis on ease of use and productivity suggest that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. The application of the toolbox to natural language processing tasks suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another possible category. The use of deep learning for image processing tasks suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a likely category. Finally, the emphasis on modularity and extensibility suggests cs.SE (Software Engineering) as a possible category.
